-- Lazard profit rises 48 pct on higher advisory fees 
-- 
-- Thu Oct 23, 2014 06:23AM EDT
-- None



Oct 23 (Reuters) - Lazard Ltd <LAZ.N> reported a 48 percent rise in quarterly profit due to a jump in advisory fees from higher M&A activity and an increase in asset management revenue.

The company's net profit rose to $89 million, or 67 cents per share, in the third quarter ended Sept. 30, from $60 million, or 45 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBwc26sd6a]